250 g Ground Beef
¾ cup Pearl Couscous
113 g Mirepoix
28 g Baby Spinach
7 g Chives
1 unit(s) Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
½ cup White Cheddar Cheese, shredded
7.5 g Beef Stock Powder
7 g Zesty Garlic Blend
2.5 g Italian Herb Spice Blend
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Heat a large pot over medium-high.
When hot, add beef and mirepoix to the dry pot. Cook for 3-5 min, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with salt and pepper.
Add half the Zesty Garlic Blend. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until fragrant.

Roughly chop spinach. (TIP: Place spinach in a bowl, then roughly chop using a pair of kitchen shears or scissors!)
Thinly slice chives.

To the pot with beef, add crushed tomatoes, stock powder, couscous, half the Italian Herb Spice Blend (use all for 4 servings), remaining Zesty Garlic Blend and 3 cups (6 cups) water. Cook for 8-10 min, stirring occasionally, until couscous is tender. (TIP: Scrape up the brown bits from the bottom of the pot; this will add extra flavour!).
Season with salt and pepper.

To the pot, add spinach and half the cheese. Stir for 30 sec, until spinach has wilted and cheese has melted.

Divide soup between bowls. Top with chives and remaining cheese.